[
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which is the explanation of the difference on that account.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            118,
            677,
            137
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A similar error appears for the equity value account because we consider indirectly  \\(8\\% = 40\\%\\)  \\*  \\(20\\%\\)  of the company A as a contribution to that account. This is too much and the equity value should be limited to  \\(40\\%\\)  of company B net equity. It is of course the same amount.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            151,
            881,
            217
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This simple group structure, without complex crossed participation, shows how weak can be the stage technique by leading to wrong consolidated figures.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            231,
            879,
            282
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1.5 Consolidation of a consortium",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            114,
            313,
            658,
            335
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A consortium group has already been defined in Part 2 Section 3.7. However, our objective in this section is to show how to consolidate such particular structure on a basis of an existing situation we met earlier.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            357,
            877,
            407
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Initially, there are two companies P1 and P2 controlled by the same physical persons. P1 and P2 are both groups of companies.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            423,
            542,
            489
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The situation we met was unfortunately a little bit more complex because P1 and P2 were owning together  \\(100\\%\\)  of a common company A. Moreover, there were also crossed participations between P1 and P2 as shown in the following structure. We already presented the consortium with a \"fictitious\" parent company FP.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            504,
            540,
            634
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "images/fd7047f43aaf6dfd1b5dea16accd352962779afa3ea525a2993dadb233015c42.jpg",
        "image_caption": [],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "bbox": [
            550,
            419,
            875,
            615
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This group will be consolidated over Year 1 (column 1) and Year 2 (column 2) on the basis of the following statutory accounts.",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            646,
            875,
            681
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Looking at the equity of each company, we confirm",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            696,
            612,
            712
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Company P1 is paying a dividend of 10",
            "- Company P2 is paying a dividend of 20",
            "Company A is paying a dividend of 30"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            150,
            728,
            569,
            809
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "And that's the reason why we already booked consolidation adjustments to eliminate group dividends.",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            825,
            875,
            859
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            65,
            372,
            80
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/df4417800d0a3d108d699640b24cc13768ae51dbb2840b5a6775692b685c5f0d.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\"></td><td colspan=\"3\">P1</td></tr><tr><td>Fin. Inv./P2</td><td>40</td><td>40</td><td>Capital</td><td>100</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>Fin. Inv./A</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>Reserves</td><td>0</td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>15</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>Result</td><td>20</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>(15)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>(4)</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>110</td><td>210</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>80</td><td>150</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
